  "prompt": "Can i send my GRE scores to the four universities freely?",
  "response": "When you take the GRE, you typically get one free score report to send to a university of your choice at the time of testing. After that, there is a fee for sending additional score reports to other universities. As of my last update, the fee was around $27 per additional score report. However, ETS (Educational Testing Service) periodically updates its policies and fees, so I recommend:\n\n1. Checking the official ETS website for current pricing\n2. Verifying the exact number of free score reports\n3. Confirming the current cost of additional score reports\n\nYou'll want to send your scores directly from the ETS system to ensure they are official and sent securely.",
